  "type": "Note",
  "number": "3.1.7",
  "title": "",
  "body": "Do you see the difference between surface area and volume?   Surface area measures the area of the of a three-dimensional object.  Volume measures the amount of the object.   Surface area is measured in square units, and volume is measured in cubic units. For example, the surface area of the cube shown at right is 6 square inches, and its volume is 1 cubic inch.  Surface Area: 6 square inches  Volume: 1 cubic inch  "
