  "body": "A triathlete wants to know the distance across a small lake, from point to point . She locates point on one side of the lake to make a right triangle as shown. The distance from to is 3 miles, and the distance from to is 4 miles. How far is it from to across the lake?   We can apply the Pythagorean theorem. Let's let represent the distance across the lake, from to . Then We square the numbers to get If 9 added to gives 16, then must be equal to 7. So must be the square root of 7. The distance across the lake is about 2.65 miles. "
